window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>A <i>Wall Street Journal</i> Top 10 national best seller </b></p> <p><b>Number one Kindle best seller in \"Mysteries &amp; Thrillers\" </b></p> <p><b>Who is hunter?</b></p> <p><b><b>Who is prey?</b> </b></p> <p><b>Who will survive?</b></p> <p>Award-winning true-crime author Robert Bidinotto makes his stunning fiction debut with a best-selling thriller that has earned more than 200 \"5-star\" rave reviews from readers. </p> <p><i>Two people, passionately in love. </i></p> <p><i>But each hides a deadly secret. </i></p> <p><i>He is a crusading vigilante, on a violent quest for justice. </i></p> <p><i>She is tracking this unknown assassin, sworn to stop him. </i></p> <p><i>Neither realizes the truth about the other. </i></p> <p><i>And neither knows that a terrifying predator is hunting them both.... </i></p> <p>From its first moments, <i>Hunter</i> takes you on a nonstop thrill ride: from the top floor of the CIA, to the marbled corridors of Capitol Hill...from the posh hotels of downtown Washington, to the city's mean, violent streets. It introduces a colorful new hero for our time - and a dazzling heroine every bit his equal. </p> <p>A spy mystery...a crime thriller...a passionate romance: <i>Hunter</i> is a genre-bending novel unlike any you've read. Deviously plotted, filled with vivid characters, and propelled at a breakneck pace, it's a tale as memorable for its provocative ideas as for a rousing climax that has readers cheering. </p> <p>If you enjoy the thrillers of Lee Child, Stephen Hunter, Brad Thor, and Vince Flynn, you'll love <i>Hunter</i>. </p>"; 
